The PBE band structures and density of states (DOSs) of c-silicyne are depicted in Figure 4a,b. Akin to graphyne, c-silicyne possesses a Dirac-like electronic property, for which the bottom conduction and top valence bands touch each other at the K point, i.e. Dirac point. The linear dispersions of bands are obtained around the Dirac point as E(k)=±ℏkvF\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
